title: Update your approved driving instructor (ADI) registration

heading_context: Update your approved driving instructor (ADI) registration
chunks.html_content:
Use this service to:

  • update your name or address on your approved driving instructor (ADI) registration
  • agree to keep your professional skills up to date
  • agree to the ADI code of practice
  • publish your details on the find driving schools, lessons and instructors service
  • view your standards check (previously called ‘check test’) history

This service is available from 6am to 11:30pm.

You need your:

  • online user ID from the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA)
  • password

You can find your user ID on letters you get from DVSA. It’s not the same as your ADI personal reference number.

Email DVSA if you’ve never had, or have lost, your user ID. You must include your:

  • ADI personal reference number or driving licence number
  • date of birth
  • postcode

heading_context: Update your approved driving instructor (ADI) registration
chunks.html_content:
You cannot use any of your 5 previously used passwords.

Your password must be at least 9 characters long. It must include at least 3 of the following:

  • uppercase characters, such as A B C
  • lowercase characters, such as a b c
  • numeric digits, such as 1 2 3
  • special characters, such as £ % &
